	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Statistics South Africa has announced the most popular names for
babies in 2017 – and at the top of the list, for both boys and girls, was Enzokuhle,
which means “do good” in Zulu. The top three names for girls were Enzokuhle, Melokuhle (“stand up
for what’s right” in Zulu) and Amahle (“pretty” in Zulu). The most common middle names for girls were Precious, Princess and Angel. Enzokuhle, Melokuhle en Amogelang were in the top five for both
genders, Stats SA reports. When it came to boys’ names, Enzokuhle was followed
in popularity by Lethabo (“luck” in Sesotho, Sepedi and Setswana) and Melokuhle. The most common middle name for boys were Junior, Blessing and Gift. In the Western Cape, Liam was the most popular name for boys and
Mia for girls. In Gauteng, Luthando was the winner for boys and Lethabo for
girls.  Stats SA also announced:  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  